itemsHeatmap.title: Comparison of Quiz Scores
itemsHeatmap.legend: Darker colors represent higher quiz scores.

scatterPlot.title: Automatic discussion forum grading versus quiz results
scatterPlot.legend:
Each dot represents the values for a student. The gray line plots the 
                              relationship between the two grading methods. The shaded area around 
                              the line is the confidence range for the line.
scatterPlot.tooltip:
Each dot represents the values for a student. The gray line plots the 
                              relationship between the two grading methods. The shaded area around 
                              the line is the confidence range for the line.

scoreDistributionByItem.title: Distribution of Quiz Scores
scoreDistributionByItem.legend:
This is a boxplot graph of quiz scores. Each dot is a student score.
                      The thickest line shows the average score for that quiz.
                      The vertical lines above and below the box show the top and lowest percent ranges.
                      See help for more detailed explanation of boxplots.
scoreDistributionByItem.tooltip:
